{"lemma":"وَقْتُ","slug":"وَقْتُ","root":"#.ق.ت","root_slug":"_-ق-ت","root_link":"/words/roots/_-ق-ت","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"وَقْت","root":"وقت","pos":"N","occurrence_count":3},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":4,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":9},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n42204","","n42206"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%88%D9%8E%D9%82%D9%92%D8%AA%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of وَقَتَ (waqata) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"time (as an abstract concept)"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"period of time, time span"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"moment, instant"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to determine, define, or place a limit on a thing especially time"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to fix boundaries of duration, to set or appoint a time for something to occur especially the falling due of an obligation"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to set a time, to appoint a time, to fix a time, to schedule"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to time"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to set a time limit"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Possibly, via dissimilation of emphatic consonants, from the root و ق ط (w q ṭ), akin to rare Classical Arabic وَقْط (waqṭ) & وَقِيطَة (waqīṭa) “hollow in a rock or mountain where rainwater collects”, dialectal Yemeni Arabic وَقَّطَ (waqqaṭa) “to cut down, break off stones”, Minaean 𐩥𐩤𐩷 (wqṭ, “cavity”), Sabaean 𐩥𐩤𐩷 (wqṭ), 𐩺𐩤𐩷 (yqṭ, “to dig up, excavate; to hollow out”), Dadanitic 𐪅𐪄𐪗 (wqṭ, “to inscribe, write”); all of these ultimately from the same biliteral Proto-Semitic root *q-ṭ emblematically represented by Arabic قَطَّ (qaṭṭa) “to cut, to carve”. The “time” sense would develop from a more original meaning of “hollow”, then “gap”, interpreted figuratively as “period or gap of time”—cf. وَقْت (waqt) in the rarely attested sense of “A space, or measure, of local extension”, perhaps a remnant of the would-be original non-temporal meaning. There also exist اِقْتَتَّ (iqtatta, “to dissect”), قَتَّ (qatta, “to reduce, to cut lengthwise”) and all derivatives of the root ق ت ت (q t t) seems to be from the meaning to cut, suggesting this origin.\nAlternatively, suggested to be borrowed from Iranian, from Proto-Indo-Iranian *bʰaktás (“distributed, allotted; lot, share”), although this etymology has some difficulties on phonological, semantic, and geographical grounds. If correct, that makes it a doublet of بَخْت (baḵt, “luck”) which was borrowed later. Compare other supposedly borrowed time terms: زَمَن (zaman), سَاعَة (sāʕa), عَام (ʕām), سَوْفَ (sawfa), أَوَان (ʔawān), إِبَّان (ʔibbān).\n\nDenominal verb of وَقْت (waqt)."},"ipa":["/waqt/","/waʔt/","/wakt/","/waɡt/","/waq.qa.ta/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n42204","headword_ar":"وَقَتَ","root":"wqt","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaqitu","text_ar":"يَقِتُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waqtN","text_ar":"وَقتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wq~t","text_ar":"وقّت","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tawoqiytN","text_ar":"تَوْقِيتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":";"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He determined, defined,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"limited,"},{"kind":"text","text":"a thing"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"as to time;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAth, L, Msb;) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"otherwise:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L, Msb:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he determined,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"defined, times."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waqatahu","text_ar":"وَقَتَهُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He declared"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"appointed"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a time in which it should be done."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waqata All~`hu AlSlaApa","text_ar":"وَقَتَ اللّٰهُ الصلَاةَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaqitu","text_ar":"يَقِتُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waq~atahaA","text_ar":"وَقَّتَهَا","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"God hath determined,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"defined, a time for prayer."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wq~t","text_ar":"وقّت","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", as also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aq~ata","text_ar":"اَقَّتَ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He assigned,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"appointed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"for a thing,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a particular time; he assigned,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"appointed, a particular time for doing"},{"kind":"text","text":"a thing. (IAth, L.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"liyawomi","text_ar":"لِيَوْمِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waq~at~uhu","text_ar":"وَقَّتُّهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ka*aA","text_ar":"كَذَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I appointed him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it, for such a day"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aj~alotuhu","text_ar":"اَجَّلْتُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S.) ―         -b2-  In the following words of the Kur. [lxxvii. 11,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waA_i*aA Alr~usulu A^uq~itato","text_ar":"وَاـِذَا الرُّسُلُ اُقِّتَتْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aqtt","text_ar":"اقتت","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a dial. form of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wuq~itato","text_ar":"وُقِّتَتْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", like as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ujuwhN","text_ar":"اُجُوهٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wujuwhN","text_ar":"وُجُوهٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S;) and the meaning is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And when the Apostles shall have one"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"particular"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"time assigned to them"},{"kind":"text","text":"to decide between the people [to whom they have been sent to preach]: (Zj:) or,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"shall be collected at their appointed time,"},{"kind":"text","text":"on the day of resurrection. (Fr.) This is the general reading: but there are other reading; namely,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wuq~itato","text_ar":"وُقِّتَتْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wuqitato","text_ar":"وُقِتَتْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, TA,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wuwqitato","text_ar":"وُوقِتَتْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which last is of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fuwEilato","text_ar":"فُوعِلَتْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlmuwaAqatapu","text_ar":"المُوَاقَتَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lamo yaqito fY Alxamori Had~FA","text_ar":"لَمْ يَقِتْ فى الخَمْرِ حَدًّا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mohammad)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"did not determine,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"define, for"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"drinking wine,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a castigation consisting of a certain number"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of blows,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"stripes"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA, from a trad.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waqata","text_ar":"وَقَتَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"sometimes signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e. God]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"made"},{"kind":"text","text":"the entering upon the state of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_iHoraAm","text_ar":"اـِحْرَام"},{"kind":"text","text":"in pilgrimage, and prayer at the commencement of its appointed time,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"obligatory,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"incumbent,"},{"kind":"text","text":"upon men. (TA.) ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"liA^aholi Almadiynapi *aA AlHulayofapi","text_ar":"لِاَهْلِ المَدِينَةِ ذَا الحُلَيْفَةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waq~ata","text_ar":"وَقَّتَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He appointed, for the people of El-Medeeneh, Dhu-l-Huleyfeh as the place where they should enter upon the state of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_iHoraAm","text_ar":"اـِحْرَام"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA, from a trad.)"}],"source_refs":["L","Msb","Zj","S","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n42206","headword_ar":"وَقْتٌ","root":"wqt","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A time;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"space,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"measure, of time,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, L, K, Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"appointed for any affair; a season:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb:) mostly used with respect to what is past: (M, K:) sometimes with respect to the future: (TA:) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"miyqaAtN","text_ar":"مِيقَاتٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K, Msb:) or, accord. to some, there is a difference between these two words; the former having an absolute signification, and the latter signifying"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a time appointed for the performance of some action:"},{"kind":"text","text":"[as in the S:] (TA:) pl. of the former"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^awoqaAtN","text_ar":"اَوْقَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and of the latter"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mawaAqiytu","text_ar":"مَوَاقِيتُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Msb.) [Hence,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waqotay^i*K","text_ar":"وَقْتَيِذٍ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Then; at that time."},{"kind":"text","text":"] ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waqotN","text_ar":"وَقْتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A space,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"measure, of local extension;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as a mile, &c. (Sb.)"}],"source_refs":["S","K","M","L","Msb","TA"]}]}}